For a truly relative `currentUrlStr` like `page.html`, `parsedUrl.protocol` is null. Then we enter the block and call `URL.parse(baseUrlStr, true, true/false)`. But `baseUrlStr` at this point has already been processed to have `http://` prefix if it started with `//`.

